.TH "lobCount" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
lobCount \- count the total number of Lobs in the current collection
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]db.collectionspace.collection.lobCount([cond])\f[]
.PP
\f[B]db.collectionspace.collection.lobCount([cond]).hint([hint])\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
SdbCollection
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This function is used to count the total number of lobs in the current
collection, users can specify the control parameters through hint.
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
The usage of the parameters \f[C]cond\f[] is used in the same way as find(), and
the \f[C]hint\f[] is used in the same way as listLobs().
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
When the function executes successfully, it will return an object of type
CLCount.
Users can get the total number of records that meet the conditions through this
object.
.PP
When the function fails, an exception will be thrown and an error message will
be printed.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
